locationDescriptions.content:

IC or ICE to Hauptbahnhof (main station) and continue with all S-Bahn trains heading east to Friedrichstrasse station (1 stop).

Airport BER: by S-Bahn or RE (Regionalexpress) to Friedrichstrasse station (approx. 30 (train) to 50 min (S-Bahn)), alternatively by airport express FEX to Ostkreuz or Hauptbahnhof and continue by S-Bahn (from Ostrkreuz 6 stops west to Friedrichstrasse, from Hauptbahnhof 1 stop east to Friedrichstrasse) (approx. 50 minutes each way)

By car: from the west and south: A100, exit Kaiserdamm - Kaiserdamm - Strasse des 17. Juni - Scheidemannstraße - Dorotheenstraße - Planckstraße (turn left).
From the southeast: B96a to Unter den Linden - Universitätsstraße (to the right) - Georgenstraße (to the left) - Planckstraße (to the right).

From the north: E55 exit Pankow direction Zentrum via Prenzlauer Promenade - Prenzlauer Allee - Unter den Linden - Universitätsstraße (to the right) - Georgenstraße (to the left) - Planckstraße (to the right).

Nearest parking garage: 200 m away, price 15 €/day

htmlDescription.htmlText:
The room has a size of 20 square meters and is part of a large three-room apartment in a residential building in the center of Berlin, built in 1900 and renovated a few years ago. It is furnished with parquet flooring, a large bed, table, desk, chairs, a wardrobe with mirror, piano, a 50 year old radio, wlan and television. The room is isolated from the other rooms of the apartment. A large, modern bathroom and a comfortable kitchen are to be shared.

The space
The apartment is located in Planckstrasse, a side street of Friedrichstrasse. Metro- and subway, railway, bus and tramway are in the immediate vicinity (2 min); important cultural institutions and sights (Museum Island, Konzerthaus, State Opera, Komische Oper, Berliner Ensemble, Deutsches Theater, Gorki-Theater, Friedrichstadt-Palast, Brandenburger Tor, Dom, Reichstag etc.) are within walking distance, for culturally interested Berlin visitors an ideal starting point for explorations.

At present, construction work is underway on a building across the street. This may cause construction noise during the day. No construction work is taking place at night.

Guest access
The guests receive keys for room, apartment and house on arrival and are then independent.

During your stay
Me or my rommate and friend Fyno are almost available in case of any request.

Other things to note
Earliest check in: 1pm or by arrangement
Latest ccheck in: 10pm
Latest check out: 11 am or by arrangement
Non-smoking apartment.
Minimum stay 2 nights.
